\[

\]

Now, we will calculate \( g(2) \) using the function \( g(x) = 3x^2 - 4x \):
\[
g(2) = 3(2^2) - 4(2) = 3(4) - 8 = 12 - 8 = 4
\]
Next, we compute \( g(g(2)) \), which is \( g(4) \):
\[
g(4) = 3(4^2) - 4(4) = 3(16) - 16 = 48 - 16 = 32
\]

Now we combine our results to find \( f(f(1)) - g(g(2)) \):
\[
f(f(1)) - g(g(2)) = 37 - 32 = 5
\]
